//EIVCHR3 - Voucher 3

On Singles day, Hoa has M voucher which gives 30% discount (maximum 50 thousands VND) for a item. The discount will apply to one item only and doesn’t apply to whole bill . Hoa willing to buy N  items at the store. How much does she need to pay?

Input

Two integer N and M (1 ≤ N, M ≤105, ) which is the number of items Hoa wants to buy and number of vouchers she have.

The second line contains N integers which are prices of N items, correspondingly. The prices is not exceed 109.

Output

The amount of money Hoa need to spend on items.

Sample

Input

Output

5 2

100000 5000 2000 100000 200000

327000

//

//tip cho bài này, bạn nên dùng đúng định lượng cho biến (int,long, double,..etc) vì bài này dễ bị time out nếu chọn sai đơn vị//
// link bài: https://www.spoj.com/EIUPROGR/problems/EIVCHR3/  //
import java.util.*;

public class EIVCHR3 {
    static Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int requirement[] = new int[2];
        double totalDis = 0;

        for (int i = 0; i < requirement.length; i++) {
            requirement[i] = sc.nextInt();
        }
        long price[] = new long[requirement[0]];
        for (int i = 0; i < price.length; i++) {
            price[i] = sc.nextLong();
            totalDis += price[i];
        }
        int times = 0;
        Arrays.sort(price);
        double discountPrice = 0;
        int n = 1;

        while (times < Math.min(requirement[1], requirement[0])) {
            discountPrice = price[price.length - n] * 0.3;
            if (discountPrice > 50000) {
                totalDis -= 50000;
            } else {
                totalDis -= discountPrice;
            }
            n++;
            times++;
        }

        System.out.println(Math.round(totalDis));
    }
}
